# Requirements

## Architecture
The Docker images in this artifact were built and tested on ARM64 (Apple
Silicon / M-series Mac) only. Reviewers on ARM64 machines can run them
natively. Reviewers on x86_64 (amd64) machines will need QEMU-based
emulation enabled for Docker (on Linux, typically via `tonistiigi/binfmt`
or `qemu-user-static`; not enabled by default), or should build the images
from source instead (see "Building from Source" in `README.MD`), which
produces a native image for their own architecture. Multi-platform
(x86_64 + ARM64) images are planned for a future version of this artifact.

## Recommended: Docker-based setup

- **Docker Desktop** 4.0 or later (includes Docker Compose v2)
  - https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/
- Approximately **2 GB** of free disk space (for Docker images and output)
- An internet connection is required only for the initial `docker compose up --build`
  to pull base images; all subsequent runs are fully offline

No other software is required when using Docker.

## Alternative: Local setup (without Docker)

### Web application
- JDK 17 or later
- Maven 3.8 or later

### Analysis scripts
- Python 3.9 or later
- The following Python packages (also listed in `requirements.txt`):
  - pandas
  - numpy
  - scipy
  - matplotlib
  - seaborn
  - openpyxl
  - statsmodels
  - pingouin

Install with:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Hardware
No special hardware is required. A standard laptop or desktop is sufficient.
The full analysis pipeline (`run_all.py`) completes in under 5 minutes on typical hardware.
